- Since (strangely) you already have your empty `.movehere` placeholders, simply target them 
- Target the old divs in groups by *all* and *colors*  
- (Use `.filter()` to filter the all into specific color groups by class-name)
- Use  i.e: `$allDIV.slice(gB*i, gB*i+gB).clone()`, with the *GroupBy* `gB` variable being set to `2` 

Use the `.append(function(index, element))` method callback. 

To explain the code `$allMH.append(i =&gt; $allDIV.slice(gB*i, gB*i+gB).clone() );`, 
Say you have 3 `#all&gt;.movehere` elements, the above will iterate three times looking like (in each iteration):

&gt; ```pseudo
&gt; (i=0): $allDIV.slice(0, 2).clone() // appended to the currently iterated DIV  
&gt; (i=1): $allDIV.slice(2, 4).clone() // appended to the currently iterated DIV  
&gt; (i=2): $allDIV.slice(4, 6).clone() // appended to the currently iterated DIV 
&gt; ```

Thanks to the implicit return of arrow function `=&gt;` the *sliced* groups are appended to the currently iterating element - directly.

### Example:


&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-js --&gt;

    jQuery($ =&gt; { // DOM ready and $ alias in scope

       const $allMH  = $(&#39;#all  &gt; .movehere&#39;),
             $redMH  = $(&#39;#red  &gt; .movehere&#39;),
             $bluMH  = $(&#39;#blue &gt; .movehere&#39;),
             $allDIV = $(&#39;#oldsection &gt; div&#39;),
             $redDIV = $allDIV.filter(&#39;.red&#39;),
             $bluDIV = $allDIV.filter(&#39;.blue&#39;),
             gB = 2; // Group by

       $allMH.append(i =&gt; $allDIV.slice(gB*i, gB*i+gB).clone() );
       $redMH.append(i =&gt; $redDIV.slice(gB*i, gB*i+gB).clone() );
       $bluMH.append(i =&gt; $bluDIV.slice(gB*i, gB*i+gB).clone() );

       $(&#39;#oldsection&#39;).empty();

     });

